<p><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/spacer.gif width=5><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/headers/current_affairs.gif><center><table width=100%><tr><td background=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/horizon_line.gif><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/spacer.gif height=16></td></tr></table><p><table Border=0 Bgcolor=#181818 Width=100%>
<tr><td colspan=2 Bgcolor=#000000 Align=center><font color=white size=+2>Shaman</font>
</td></tr><tr><td width=10% Bgcolor=#101010 Align=center Valign=top><table width=200><tr><td align=center><font size=-1><table><tr><td align=center><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_top.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_left.jpg><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/portraits/INDAN.jpg width="104" height="184"><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_right.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_bottom.jpg></td></tr></table>Legendary  INDAN<br>Level 65 Shaman<br><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_11.gif" title="Silver Order of Leadership"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_6.gif" title="Order of Meritorious Service"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_6.gif" title="Order of Meritorious Service"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_7.gif" title="Star of Achievement"><br>Webmaster<br><a style="text-decoration:none;" href="main.cgi?fetch=INDAN"><font size=-1 color="#DDDDDD">INDAN</font></a><font size=-1>'S LINEAGE</font><br><img src='http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/bio.gif' border=0></font></td></tr></table></td><td width=90% Valign=top><a href=main.cgi?followup=14&forum=9><p align=right><font color=#cccccc>Reply | </a><a href=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/guild-builder/call/main.cgi?action=messages&forum=9><font color=#cccccc>Return</a></p><br clear=all><p><i>I saw this board and thought I should say something on Shamans.<br><br>Im not the best solo shaman.  I can hold my own but Ive never really tried it much since level 54.  <br><br>Ive seen that most people that play Shamans are quiet and reserved.<br><br>The class is amazing and you dont get a real feel for it till after level 58.<br><br>Ive met anumber of shamans that get mad at being thought of as just slowers.  Ive never payed that much mind because if more people played shamans sony/verant would nerf us.  The fact is that our capablities when properly played are tremendous beyond most classes belief. <br><br> I never worry about mana unless I have to slow right after buffing awhole raid (I was still able to slow - Just was worried about mana). <br><br>Hp is your friend.. kei is nice but health is more important.  Health is mana and with torpor.  It is virtually unlimited (altho you will notice life easier with kei)<br><br>Im a firm believer in always haveing slow up on my spell list. As well as torpor.  <br><br>Most shamans get bored in a raid or group if another is present.  This is true but most dont realize this changes their function.  your are now a dotter.<br><br>The fastest I have ever killed stuff in Seb is with three shamans and a rogue. One shaman slowed and two dot stacked. We killed mobs faster than I have ever seen and got good cash.  The rogue picked locks.. <br><br>Shaman dots stack not only by person but by spell line too.  Our poison line will stack all the way up as well as our desease line.  This makes our damage out put per tick above most rangers when stacked properly and does not include damage by our dog.<br><br>In most raids lately Ive been main slower.  In HOT you cant slow them all.<br><br>I start with a desease slow then malo then turgurs. One will usually stick.  Some will just not stick.<br>IF there is more than one shaman there have them slow too. After you though so they dont get agro.  Someones will hit .. Ive seen a 54 slow a mob that resisted a 63 five times in a row.<br><br>Watch your agro.  Let the tank get hit a bit before slowing.  also try maloing your mob as its being pulled in .. that way you can slow it faster as it hits the tank.<br><br>Put yourself near a wall when slowing if possible.  Mobs can disrupt your casting by moving you.  IF your on a wall they cant push you and disrupt your casting.<br><br>Sometimes you will slow a mob that a enchanter/druid/mage will charm. Casting cure desease will remove your slow and speed it up.<br><br>cancell magic does not work on your slows but will remove enchanter slows.  Sometimes its nice to annul a mob till you break your own root .. your slow will still be there and the mob will be debuffed.<br><br>Your slow is faster then your heal.  remember slowing the mob may save that tank when your heal would not be able to.<br><br><br>You get a nifty spell called vison.  This will bond your sight to your target.  This is nice when your pets on something and you want to see it.  But my most common use of it is to find corpses.  If a char just recently died in your group, click on his name.<br>His corpse will show on your target window. cast vision and pop your looking thru the eyes of a corpse.  Then use your external cameras to find where it is.  <br><br>Wall buggs -  if you go into bear form and cast shrink twice on your self you can look thru most walls<br><br><br>I will be adding to this as I wake up (its later here) and remeber more.<br><br>I hope this helped you some. <br><br>Indan<br><br clear=all></i><br></td></tr><tr><td>
